00:07:32.120 --> 00:07:32.760
<v Speaker 1>Trabajar.

00:07:32.760 --> 00:07:35.640
<v Speaker 1>How would you say I'm tired of working?

00:07:36.380 --> 00:07:39.420
<v Speaker 2>Estoy cansada de trabajar.

00:07:40.140 --> 00:07:43.580
<v Speaker 1>Estoy cansada de trabajar.

00:07:45.240 --> 00:07:57.960
<v Speaker 1>For one of the pasts that we saw, for the line in the past, so when we're referring to like a period of time in the past, for our verbs we had the abba base ending.

00:07:57.740 --> 00:08:01.660
<v Speaker 1>So how would you say I was from a star?

00:08:01.820 --> 00:08:02.620
<v Speaker 1>Staba.

00:08:03.740 --> 00:08:05.660
<v Speaker 1>I was tired of working

00:08:07.380 --> 00:08:10.420
<v Speaker 2>Estaba cansada de trabajar.

00:08:10.420 --> 00:08:13.460
<v Speaker 1>Estaba cansada de trabajar.

00:08:13.460 --> 00:08:13.780
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:08:13.780 --> 00:08:15.060
<v Speaker 1>I was tired of working.

00:08:15.060 --> 00:08:15.780
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:08:15.780 --> 00:08:18.100
<v Speaker 1>We were tired of working.

00:08:18.100 --> 00:08:21.300
<v Speaker 1>And let's be a masculine or a mixed group.

00:08:21.139 --> 00:08:24.820
<v Speaker 1>We were tired of working.

00:08:28.259 --> 00:08:29.060
<v Speaker 1>Very good.

00:08:32.180 --> 00:08:33.300
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:08:32.940 --> 00:08:42.300
<v Speaker 1>If you want to say something like it's a way of doing it, it's a way of doing it, the word for way is form.

00:08:42.320 --> 00:08:44.240
<v Speaker 1>form, a form of doing it.

