<v Speaker 1>Actualmente means currently, at the moment, rather than actually.

00:11:08.920 --> 00:11:18.600
<v Speaker 1>Mostly the vocabulary, the Latin English that we turn into Spanish is very reliable, but there are a few words that we want to watch out for.

00:11:18.720 --> 00:11:20.320
<v Speaker 1>Discutir is one of them.

00:11:20.320 --> 00:11:24.240
<v Speaker 1>This doesn't really mean to discuss as much as it does to argue.

00:11:24.240 --> 00:11:27.520
<v Speaker 1>So I don't believe in arguing.

00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:31.520
<v Speaker 2>No creo in discutir.

00:11:31.520 --> 00:11:32.240
<v Speaker 2>Good.

00:11:32.240 --> 00:11:33.280
<v Speaker 1>In this way.

00:11:33.280 --> 00:11:37.600
<v Speaker 1>We will say of this way rather than in this way.

00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:40.440
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:11:40.440 --> 00:11:45.080
<v Speaker 1>So altogether I don't believe in arguing, in discussing in this way

00:11:46.680 --> 00:11:52.200
<v Speaker 2>No creo in discutir de esta forma.

00:11:52.200 --> 00:11:52.839
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:11:52.839 --> 00:11:56.839
<v Speaker 1>No creo in discutir de esta forma.

00:11:56.839 --> 00:11:57.800
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:11:57.900 --> 00:12:10.300
<v Speaker 1>So with this sentence, gracias por venir, we are reminded how we have two words for for, por and para, and we need to have a think and decide which one we think is most appropriate before we translate for.

00:12:10.300 --> 00:12:10.620
<v Speaker 1>And

00:12:11.220 --> 00:12:19.300
<v Speaker 1>that after prepositions we don't need to worry about making the ing form of the verb we just use the to form

